  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 13:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] \ud83d\udc1b ZOMBIE ROOT CAUSE: Old bash Parents from Mar 30 Spawning Infinite Orphans\n\n**Task:** Find what keeps spawning 2 new trading_bot orphans every 5 minutes despite watchdog killing them.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:**\nTwo zombie `bash` processes from Mar 30 were still alive as parents:\n- **PID 3837970** \u2014 `/bin/bash /home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/start-pm-bot.sh` (Mar 30)\n- **PID 3908042** \u2014 `bash scripts/start-pm-bot.sh` (Mar 30)\n\nThese were OLD screen sessions that got killed (`screen -X quit`) but the bash child survived because the old start-pm-bot.sh didn't use `exec`. When screen died, bash got orphaned to init (PID 772). Every time their python child got killed, **bash restarted python** because the old script had no `exec` \u2014 it was running python as a subprocess that bash would wait for, and when it died, bash's loop or the script itself would re-execute.\n\n**Timeline of the bug:**\n1. Mar 30: Multiple screen restarts \u2192 bash processes orphaned\n2. Each bash process periodically respawned python \u2192 2 extra bots\n3. My zombie killer killed the python children \u2192 bash respawned them in seconds\n4. Infinite cycle: kill python \u2192 bash respawns \u2192 kill python \u2192 bash respawns\n\n**Fix:** `kill -9 3837970 3908042` \u2014 killed the zombie bash parents. Combined with:\n1. `start-pm-bot.sh` now uses `exec` (replaces bash with python \u2014 no parent to respawn)\n2. Watchdog rewritten to be cleaner and use `restart_pm_bot()` helper that kills ALL processes before starting fresh\n3. No more orphan parents possible with `exec`\n\n**Verification:** Only PID 4179862 (legit screen child) remains. No old bash parents.\n\n**This was the REAL bug all along.** Not asyncio, not duplicate event loops, not code issues. Old bash scripts from previous screen sessions, orphaned to init, infinitely respawning python children.\n\n**Next:** Confirm clean state persists through next 2 watchdog cycles (13:40, 13:45).\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Process Management Fixed \u2014 Single Bot Instance Enforced\n\n**Task:** Fix the multi-process zombie bug found in P2 and prevent recurrence.\n\n**Problem:** Killing zombie PIDs created a cascade \u2014 watchdog saw \"pm-bot DEAD\", restarted, spawned more zombies. The `bash -c \"cd ... && source ... && python3 ...\"` screen command created orphan subprocesses.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. **`scripts/start-pm-bot.sh`** \u2014 Clean startup script using `exec` to replace bash with python (no intermediate subshells). Kills any stale trading_bot processes before starting.\n2. **`scripts/bot-watchdog.sh`** \u2014 Zombie killer rewritten to use `pstree` to identify the legitimate screen-owned python PID. Kills only orphan processes.\n3. **All watchdog screen restarts** now use `start-pm-bot.sh` instead of inline `bash -c`.\n\n**Verification:** `pstree` shows clean tree: `screen \u2192 python3 (1 thread)`. No orphans.\n\n**Remaining issue:** Single python process still produces 3x loop ",
